video_title: This Is How Your Dreams Work
transcript:
this is how dreams work so when you've
got a bunch of emotions when you stop
and dream what happens is you feel those
emotions if someone's chasing you in a
dream you're actually really scared
right like that fear is 100 real if
there's lust in a dream like I don't
know if you've had those kind of dreams
but like you know what I'm saying like
that that's some that's some good
dreaming right there but so really what
happens when we dream is the emotions
that we feel are real it's not about
like the circumstances of the dream so
there was like I was driving a car and
then a giant tooth came and smashed my
car and then once I was smashed in the
car I turned into a rabbit and then I
flew up into the sky and I saw the eye
of God and the eye of God was crying all
that like imagery crap I don't think
there's a whole lot of very solid
scientific evidence that like the tooth
means something and the eye of God means
something but what we do know more
scientifically is that the emotions that
you've stored up throughout your time
during the day or your life will come
out in dreams
